.TH CDI_RCV_MSG 3 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "OpenSS7 CDI API Library"
.\" =========================================================================
.SH NAME
.B cdi_rcv_msg
\- receive a message.
.\"
.\"
.SH INTERFACE
.PP
.BR libdlpiapi (3),
the
.IR GCOM -specific,
CDI
.[
cdi revision 0.9.2
.]
API Library.
.[
cdiapi
.]
.\"
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.ad l
.nh
.PP
.B #include <sys/cdi.h>
.br
.B #include <cdiapi.h>
.HP \w'\fBint\ cdi_rcv_msg\fP('u
\fBint\ cdi_rcv_msg\fP(\fBint\fP\ \fIfd\fP, \fBchar\ *\fP\fIbuf\fP, \fBint\fP\ \fInbytes\fP, \fBlong\fP\ \fIflags\fP);
.ad b
.hy
.\"
.\"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.PP
.TP \w'\fInbytes\fP\(em'u
.I fd
the file descriptor for the Stream.
.TP
.I buf
a buffer into which to receive the data portion of the message.
.TP
.I nbytes
the length of the buffer.
.TP
.I flags
flags indicating which messages to expect.  This argument can be a bitwise OR of
zero or more of the following flags:
.RS
.TP \w'\fBReturn_modem_sig_ind\fP\(em'u
.B Return_error_ack
.PD 0
.TP
.B Return_info_ack
return on \fBCD_INFO_ACK\fP(7).
.TP
.B Return_unidata_ack
return on \fBCD_UNITDATA_ACK\fP(7).
.TP
.B Return_error_ind
return on \fBCD_ERROR_IND\fP(7).
.TP
.B Return_disable_con
return on \fBCD_DISABLE_CON\fP(7).
.TP
.B Return_enable_con
return on \fBCD_ENABLE_CON\fP(7).
.TP
.B RetryOnSignal
retry on [\fBEINTR\fP] or [\fBERESTARTSYS\fP].
.TP
.B Return_ok_ack
return on \fBCD_OK_ACK\fP(7).
.TP
.B Return_bad_frame_ind
return on \fBCD_BAD_FRAME_IND\fP(7).
.TP
.B Return_modem_sig_ind
return on \fBCD_MODEM_SIG_IND\fP(7).
.PD
.RE
.\"
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B cdi_rcv_msg
is a CDI API Library
.[
cdiapi
.]
subroutine.
.\"
.\"
.SH USAGE
.PP
To use the
.B cdi_rcv_msg
function, include
.RB < sys/cdi.h >
and
.RB < cdiapi.h >
header files in C language programs.
Add the
.RB ` -lcdiapi '
flag to the linker command when linking C language programs that use the
.B cdi_rcv_msg
function.
.\"
.\"
.SH MT CONTEXT
.PP
.B cdi_rcv_msg
is fully thread-safe.
What is described as global variables are in fact thread-specific data when
linked with
.BR libpthread .
.\"
.\"
.SH RETURN
.PP
When
.B cdi_rcv_msg
is successful, it returns zero (0) or a positive integer value.
When
.B cdi_rcv_msg
fails, it returns a negative integer value (-1).
.\"
.\"
.SH ERRORS
.PP
When
.B cdi_rcv_msg
fails, it returns a negative integer value (-1).
.B cdi_rcv_msg
may fail when:
.TP \w'[\fBENOMEM\fP]\(em'u
.RB [ EBADF ]
the file descriptor,
.IR fd ,
supplied does not correspond to a valid CDI Stream open for reading and
writing.
.TP
.RB [ EINVAL ]
one or more of the arguments are invalid.
.PP
In addition, any of the error number returned by
.BR cdi_get_a_msg (3)
can be returned by
.BR cdi_rcv_msg .
.\"
.\"
.SH NOTICES
.PP
.B cdi_rcv_msg
is a
.IR GCOM -specific
function.  It may be necessary to define the C preprocessor symbol,
.BR _GCOM_SOURCE ,
before including the
.RB < sys/cdi.h >
header file,
to expose this symbolic constants, data structures and declarations necessary
for the use of this function.
It may also be necessary to include the
.RB < cdiapi.h >
header file
to expose this symbolic constants, data structures and declarations necessary
for the use of this function.
.\"
.\"
.SH FILES
.PP
.TP
.B @includedir@/@PACKAGE@/sys/cdi.h
The CDI header file.
.TP
.B @includedir@/@PACKAGE@/cdiapi.h
The CDI API Library header file.
.TP
.B @libdir@/libcdiapi.a
The static library containing the
.BR cdi_rcv_msg
function.
.TP
.B @libdir@/libcdiapi.so
The shared object library containing the
.BR cdi_rcv_msg
function.
.\"
.\"
.SH BUGS
.PP
.B cdi_rcv_msg
has no known bugs.
.\"
.\"
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
.BR cdi (7),
.BR cdiapi (3),
.IR STREAMS (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH COMPATIBILITY
.PP
.B cdi_rcv_msg
is compatible with the
.I GCOM
CDI API Library,
.[
npiapi
.]
and system providing an interface equivalent to the
.I GCOM
CDI API Library,
with the following portability considerations:
.IP \(em \w'\(em\(em'u
.B CDI API Library
functions are
.IR GCOM -specific,
and are provided only for porting
.IR GCOM
software to
.BR Linux .
They are inherently non-portable.  These functions will be avoided by portable
CDI programs.
.IP \(em
Binary compatibility is not attempted, only source compatibility: any binary
compatibility experienced is coincidental and may change on a future release.
It may be necessary to recompile all \fISTREAMS\fP drivers and modules that
share definitions with the CDI API library using
.B @PACKAGE_TITLE@
supplied header files.
.PP
For further compatibility information, see
.BR cdiapi (3),
.BR cdi (7),
.IR STREAMS (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH CONFORMANCE
.PP
CDI,
.[
cdi revision 0.9.2
.]
and
.I GCOM
CDI API documentation.
.[
cdiapi
.]
